most of the time. If it's the analyst, they want to know what models worked and didn't work.

00:19:07.839 --> 00:19:13.439
And so you need to make sure that synthesizing into the one point that you're trying to make,

00:19:13.439 --> 00:19:16.400
and then going from there, rather than saying, I have all this information,

00:19:16.959 --> 00:19:20.400
and I need to bring it down. So starting from that core point,

00:19:20.400 --> 00:19:23.119
and branching out from there, tends to be the way I direct people.

00:19:25.520 --> 00:19:31.359
Question from anonymous, importantly. What should I do if my corporation has a terrible

00:19:31.359 --> 00:19:35.280
color branding screen? Quit. No, I'm just kidding.

00:19:37.040 --> 00:19:43.680
I've worked with our brand team to try and develop sort of alternate colors that I can

00:19:43.680 --> 00:19:50.800
use in reports. Our standard color palette is not great for color blindness. And we have red and

00:19:50.800 --> 00:19:54.160
blue. And I'm like, everything has to be in our red, white, and blue color scheme. And I'm like,

00:19:54.160 --> 00:19:58.479
well, now everything that's red is important. And so I've tried to be like, OK, well,

00:19:58.479 --> 00:20:03.040
what greens can we use that aren't related to our color palette? And I've worked with that design

00:20:03.040 --> 00:20:06.880
group, and they trust me. And again, these are mostly internal documents, so I don't need to

00:20:06.880 --> 00:20:13.280
adhere to our theme in the world. But again, collaboration is the key to the game.

00:20:13.680 --> 00:20:17.760
And then also, you've got a brand book, so pick some of the other colors.

00:20:20.079 --> 00:20:22.160
Ways to work around it. Thank you.

00:20:28.239 --> 00:20:32.160
And let's welcome our next speakers, Aaron Chaffetz and Karishma.

